# dplyr5000

The package contains a tibble with 5000 rows, one for each of the first 5000 
travis builds of [dplyr](https://github.com/tidyverse/dplyr). 

```{r}
library(dplyr)
# remotes::install_github("romainfrancois/dplyr5000")
library(dplyr5000)

dplyr5000 %>% 
  group_by(state) %>% 
  tally(sort = TRUE)
```
